\caption{Source: SemiAnalysis}
\end{figure}
The DSP chip is one of if not the most power-hungry and expensive components within the transceiver. For an 800G SR8 Transceiver -- the DSP accounts for nearly \textasciitilde{}50\% of the module’s total power consumption, which is why there has been so much focus on getting rid of the DSP.

